answerText: Rolling Stones[10] This band from Boston, led by Steven Tyler, hit it big with their 1975 album Toys in the Attic. That album features the song "Walk This Way," which was later covered by Run-D.M.C.

subject: Trash
question: Question: One of this band's founders, Brian Jones, was dismissed from the band in 1969 and died shortly after.  [10] Name this British rock band, which takes its name from a song by Muddy Waters. Mick Jagger leads this band, whose songs include "Sympathy for the Devil."
